Title: The Way of the Intercepting Fist
Description: Mike enlists the teachings of martial arts expert Li Tsung in order to defend himself despite his blindness.
Short Description: Mike enlists the teachings of martial arts expert Li Tsung in order to defend himself despite his blindness.

Title: A World of Perfect Complicity
Description: Mike and Nikki go undercover as husband and wife in an exclusive apartment building, in an attempt to discover the identity of a thief who is robbing its wealthy residents.
Short Description: Mike and Nikki go undercover as husband and wife to stop a thief.

Title: So, Who's Fred Hornbeck?
Description: A man who spent several years in prison for a murder he didn't commit enlists Mike's help in finding the real killer.
Short Description: Mike helps an ex-con beat a murder rap.

Title: Elegy in Brass
Description: When Mike begins investigating the murder of a Jazz Society director and the theft of two rare and valuable instruments, it leads him on a path into greed, ambition, hidden family secrets and the world of jazz music.
Short Description: Mike investigates the murder of a Jazz Society director.

Title: Spell Legacy Like Death
Description: A dying man sets bombs around the city, and then calls Mike demanding $500,000 in ransom money. Mike suspects the bomber is someone from a case he worked in the past, as he meets with the bomber to pay the ransom.
Short Description: Mike stops a bomber, who is a former client.

Title: The Shape of Nightmares
Description: A young widow asks Mike to look into the apparent suicide of her husband, who died in prison.
Short Description: A young widow asks Mike to look into the apparent suicide of her husband, who died in prison.

Title: The Girl with the Broom
Description: A Rembrandt is stolen from a wealthy couple's home, and the owner doesn't think a blind insurance investigator is able to handle the job. Mike's investigation into the theft takes him into a web of hidden family secrets and lies.
Short Description: Mike investigates the theft of a sceptical couple's stolen Rembrandt.

Title: Wednesday's Child
Description: Nikki is kidnapped after purchasing an antique sewing machine at an auction, and held for ransom. Mike must discover what's hidden within the machine that's of value, and then with Li's help find a way to rescue Nikki.
Short Description: Nikki is kidnapped. Mike must come to rescue.

Title: I See', Said the Blind Man
Description: Mike overhears a woman being killed in a darkened alley, and sends Pax to help her. Pax is critically stabbed, and the attacker simply walks away, realizing Mike is blind. Longstreet must try to find out who the killer is.
Short Description: Mike's dog, Pax, is stabbed trying to save a victim.

Title: This Little Piggy Went to Marquette
Description: Mike investigates a series of thefts of semi-truck trailers (known as "pigs") and uncovers a ring of thieves.
Short Description: Mike investigates a series of thefts of semi-truck trailers.

Title: There Was a Crooked Man
Description: A valuable racehorse is stolen and held for ransom. The kidnappers want Mike to deliver the ransom money, because they figure he won't be able to identify them.
Short Description: Kidnappers try to use Mike's blindness for cover in kidnap for ransom.

Title: The Old Team Spirit
Description: There has been a series of armored-car robberies, and Mike's old mentor, Harold Kemp, is in charge of the investigation. As Mike assists Harold in the investigation, he begins to suspect his mentor is involved.
Short Description: Mike suspects his mentor in a string of armored car robberies.

Title: The Long Way Home
Description: Harper Electronics specializes in hiring handicapped employees, but the company is hit with a string of robberies. Going undercover to investigate, Mike becomes an employee with the firm.
Short Description: Mike helps a company end a string of robberies.

Title: Let the Memories Be Happy Ones
Description: Mike finally meets his sister-in-law Hannah, but their encounter is marred by an attempt on the life of Hannah's husband Sven, who is with the Swedish State Department and currently involved in sensitive discussions with other countries.
Short Description: Mike's sister-in-law, Hannah's husband has his life threatened.

Title: Survival Times Two
Description: Mike and Duke are stranded in the bayou while on a fishing trip. Duke is bitten by a water moccasin and falls deathly ill, forcing Mike to find a way to survive in the wild and fend off a crazed Cajun trying to kill them.
Short Description: Duke is bitten by a water moccasin in the bayou, and Mike must save him.

Title: Eye of the Storm
Description: Mike travels to a lonely roadside diner to meet the representative of a gang that stole a valuable jade chess set, in order to pay the ransom for its return.
Short Description: Mike confronts a gang in a ransom heist.

Title: Please Leave the Wreck for Others to Enjoy
Description: Nikki is run down by a hit-and-run driver while working on a case with Mike, placing her in the hospital in critical condition.
Short Description: Nikki is hit by a car and is in critical condition.

Title: Anatomy of a Mayday
Description: When Mike's friend Barry sends out a mayday and then disappears at sea, Mike feels someone may have tried to murder him.
Short Description: Mike investigates friend Barry's attempted murder at sea.

Title: Sad Songs and Other Conversations
Description: When a fire breaks out in a hospital room, the patient inside dies. Mike investigates and suspects arson, but must sift through several suspects to find out who and why.
Short Description: Mike investigates hospital patient's death in room fire.

Title: Field of Honor
Description: Mike's good friend Jim Collins is the starting quarterback for the New Orleans football team and gets severely beaten in a high stakes game of football bribery.
Short Description: Mike helps an old football friend.

Title: Through Shattering Glass
Description: When Mike hears a man being murdered, he pieces together enough clues to guess the killer's identity.
Short Description: When Mike hears a man being murdered, he pieces together enough clues to guess the killer's identity.

Title: Beginnings
Description: The story of Michael Longstreet, an insurance investigator recovering from an explosion that killed his wife and took his sight.
Short Description: The story of Michael Longstreet, an insurance investigator recovering from an explosion that killed his wife and took his sight.
